<subSubSection id="E90CC45257604C5975ED52812A2521A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="E739AF4A611D6606AC3DC072ACEBFFE4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1FED62E760FC985BE3135C640D20E397" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Erect or decumbent perennial from an often somewhat tufted woody rootstock with several stems from base, stems glabrous or obscurely pubescent, sometimes rooting at the nodes. Leaves petiolate, 4-12 
<normalizedToken id="D2D7768689B50B54823E490CFC212D19" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.2-0.7 cm, linear or linear-lanceolate, finely acuminate, acute, apiculate, base cuneate to subrounded, glabrous; petioles 0.5-2.5 cm long, glabrous to sparsely pilose. Inflorescence of solitary (rarely paired) flowers from the uppermost leaf axils, or apparently terminal; peduncles 0.5-4 cm; bracteoles filiform, 2-5 mm; pedicels 7-10 mm; sepals subequal, 4-7 mm long, lanceolate, finely acuminate, glabrous, margins scarious; corolla 3-4 cm long, pink, funnel-shaped from pale tube 10-15 mm long, glabrous, limb c. 3 cm diam. unlobed but toothed at tips of midpetaline bands. Capsules 7-8 mm, glabrous, globose, usually 2-seeded; seeds 4.5 
<normalizedToken id="FC5CAB01229C6370EFBE36783EEF7111" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, minutely pubescent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
